name: Harvest Tesla Enhanced High Income Shares ETF
longDescription: In order to achieve its investment objectives, Harvest Tesla Enhanced High Income Shares ETF will invest up to 100% of its total assets (including assets acquired with borrowings), directly or indirectly, in the common stock of Tesla and will write covered call options on shares of Tesla. The proportion of covered call options written will vary depending on market conditions and will be based on the Harvest ETFs distribution policy, subject to a maximum 50% write level. The Harvest ETFs covered call strategy will be reviewed monthly to ensure cash flow sustainability according to the Harvest ETFs distribution policy. Harvest Tesla Enhanced High Income Shares ETF is considered an alternative mutual fund within the meaning of NI 81-102 and is permitted to invest in asset classes or use investment strategies that are not permitted for other types of mutual funds.
fulldescription: In order to achieve its investment objectives, Harvest Tesla Enhanced High Income Shares ETF will invest up to 100% of its total assets (including assets acquired with borrowings), directly or indirectly, in the common stock of Tesla and will write covered call options on shares of Tesla. The proportion of covered call options written will vary depending on market conditions and will be based on the Harvest ETFs distribution policy, subject to a maximum 50% write level. The Harvest ETFs covered call strategy will be reviewed monthly to ensure cash flow sustainability according to the Harvest ETFs distribution policy. Harvest Tesla Enhanced High Income Shares ETF is considered an alternative mutual fund within the meaning of NI 81-102 and is permitted to invest in asset classes or use investment strategies that are not permitted for other types of mutual funds. As an alternative mutual fund, under NI 81-102, Harvest Tesla Enhanced High Income Shares ETF is permitted to use strategies generally prohibited by conventional mutual funds, including the ability to invest more than 10% of its NAV in securities of a single issuer, the ability to borrow cash, to short sell beyond the limits prescribed for conventional mutual funds and to employ leverage. While these specific strategies will be used in accordance with Harvest Tesla Enhanced High Income Shares ETFs investment objectives and strategies, during certain market conditions they may accelerate the pace at which an investment decreases in value. ETF will seek to provide Unitholders with longterm capital appreciation
